text: Beyza (, also Romanized as Beyzā, Beyẕā, and Bayzâ; also known as Beyẕā, Baiza, Beyẕā, and is a city and capital of Central District (Beyza County), in Beyza County, Fars Province, Iran. At the 2006 census, its population was 3,593, in 845 families. == References == Category:Cities in Sepidan County
title: Beyza
